rComments: To be fair, the material and his tests aren't hard.His lectures are disorganized and boring, but his review sessions before exams are helpful, as tests are repetitive. Basically, memorize lecture notes, online notes and textbook readings, write EVERYTHING during exam, then you should be able to get a B.
He posts all useful information on the website so going to class isn't that helpful. Very boring class although he does make an effort with use of office hours for help. Did not enjoy this course. :(
No good

Not the most articulate of professors, but Denny does make the effort in explaining things. The material is interesting and relavent. He is most helpful with questions durring class.

This guy's actually not as bad as people think.  He teaches you what you need to know in his tests, and that's about it.  No digressions or small take.  Paying attention in class can get you an easy B, for a 300 level class.

Come on people! His tests and exams are EASY, same stuff as previous years.  True-lectures are useless. However, he replies to emails fast and could be reached during office hours, as long as you MAKE AN EFFORT. :) I say-go for it, easy course, easy grade. Just do the readings.
When's he going to retire? He is LAZY and totally not APPROACHABLE. He doesn't reply emails and doesn't know what he's teaching.  His tests are hard. Definitely not recommended.
the worst lectures I have had in my whole life. I can't believe they allow him to teach... worse they pay him...

stutters, not willing to help at all, lazy. People asked for answers to questions so as to get an idea of what he expect. He stutters and says he look into it. We never got the answers and his excuse was he didn't do it. WTF? Tests questions were vague. Paid $750 to teach myself.
